                                Report abuseTranscript of Robert W. "Bob"  Pittman  Robert W. "Bob"  Pittman  MTVOn August 1st, 1981 MTV, (Music Television) aired for the first time and was originally only available to households on New Jersey. MTV then became an influential source of pop culture and entertainment in the United States and other parts of the world including Europe, Asia and Latin America, which all have MTV- branded channels. Back Round MTV *Born December 28. 1953*Radio announcer at age 15 *CEO of Clear Channel Communications, AOL, Six Flags Theme Park, Quantum Media, Century 21 Real Estate and Time Warner Enterprise. *Also COO of American Online, Inc. and AOL Time Warner. *Growth of nickelodeon *August 1st, 1981, MTV In MTV's early days, its programming consisted of basic music videos that were provided by free record companies. As the record industry saw MTV as a, "promotional vehicle" money was quickly invested in making more exciting and creative videos. MTV was important in promoting the careers of performers such as Madonna, Michael Jackson and Prince, whose videos played continuously. By the late 1980s, MTV started airing non-video programming that strayed toward teen audiences. MTV quickly developed a reputation of pushing the cultural boundaries. Historically MTV revolutionized the music industry.VH1 Fuse MTV2 CMT  Video Music Awards Celebrities Nothing to go from Geographical MTV studios is located in Broadway, NY. Available any where in the world GovernmentalFCC EconomicallyHigh RatingsAdsAs MTV rapidly grew more popular, it was easier to raiser awareness for many causes occurring around the world. "It's Your Sex Life" Campaign "Fight For Your Rights: Take a Stand Against Discrimination.""Choose or loose"ImpactsVery Popular Influential Raises Awareness Negative ImpactsBad influences on younger audiencesPittman no longer works for MTV. He now focuses his time on Clear Channel Communications. MTV is the largest television network of its time. It reaches about 264 million households in 140 countries. CitationsMazzaccaro , Brianna . "Robert Pittman ." Father of MTV. Junior Division Group Website . Web. 8 Oct 2013. <http://robertpittmanmtv.weebly.com/>."Robert Pittman ." Wikipedia . N.p., 8 October 2013. Web. 8Oct 2013. <http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Robert_Pittman_(media_executive)>."MTV launches ." History . N.p., n.d. Web. 8 Oct 2013. <http://www.history.com/this-day-in-history/mtv-launches>.Full transcriptMore presentations by
    
        
